<MudText Typo="@Typo.h5">
    Difficulty Rating & Passive Checks
</MudText>

<br />

<MudGrid>
    <MudItem xs="6">
        <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
            Certain actions require players to make a Skill Check in order to determine whether they are successful, but there is nothing to “contest” that roll. In that case, a Difficulty Rating (DR) is used.
            <br />
            <br />
            <b>Proficiency Tier for Passive DR</b> denotes what is the Difficulty Rating based on the specific Skill Proficiency Tier for Passive Checks against that Skill.
            <br />
            <br />
            e.g. When a character is trying to sneak past a guard who is not actively searching for intruders, they will make a Subterfuge check against guard’s Passive Perception DR. If the guard has Adept Proficiency in Perception, the DR for that check is set as 6.            <br />
        </MudText>
    </MudItem>
