<MudText Typo="@Typo.h5">
    Success Tiers
</MudText>

<br />

<MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
    <b>Success Tier</b> denotes how well a character has done on a particular skill check. A character is said to met a Success Tier for each increment of 4 they have exceeded the Difficulty Rating of the check.
    <br />
    <br />
    Certain features grant additional benefits for each Success Tier. For example, Forage Rest Action grants more gathered materials for each Success Tier.
</MudText>

<br />
<br />

<MudText Typo="@Typo.h5">
    Group Checks
</MudText>

<br />

<MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
    When the entire party of characters attempts to engage in a particular activity, the GM may call for a <b>Group Check</b>.
    <br />
    <br />
    When a Group Check is called, the entire party rolls the Skill Check. If half or more of the rolls beat the DR (or contested roll), it is considered that the entire party succeeded.
    <br />
    <br />
    Every additional success after meeting the prerequisites is considered to increase Success Tier of the overall roll.
    <br />
    <br />
    If a character rolls double the DR of the check, it counts as an additional success.
</MudText>

